This area, known as the Berkley and Bradford Hills Section, is located south of Genessee Street and extends from Cumberland all the way to Clairvue Avenues (also a small square of land lying east of Oakwood cemetery.) It is beautifully laid out and the terrain is rolling and hilly. The area is 50% developed; all utilities installed; transportation is only fair; there are no schools in the area. The finer and more expensive homes are situated in the section adjacent to Oakwood Cemetery; that section lying west of Arlington Avenue is older and, naturally, the demand for homes here has been weak. The northwest corner of the area (Scottholm Blvd. district) has witnessed Jewish (high class) infiltration during the past 4-5 years; some are now moving into the Bradford Hills section. The areas best features are: (1) excellent lay-out; (2) appealing terrains; (3) well constructed homes; (4) good prospects for future development; (5) high percentage of home owners. Adverse: (1) lack of adequate schools; (2) Semitic infiltration. Rated a good first grade area in view of the several favorable factors mentioned above.  Typical Sales: |Address| Type Property| Sales Price & Terms| Remarks| (
