This section is about 85% developed on level to slightly rolling ground. Area is convenient to transportation, school, a park, churches and local shopping facilities. Stores and commercial properties are prohibited but there is a new Regional market nearby, and on Court Street some business has developed by special permit. Population is slowly increasing as the section experiences an infiltration of good class Italian families. Houses are built rather closely together on 40-45 foot lots and are comparatively homogeneous in design, although there are many small frame houses in the neighborhood. Objectionable factors include odors wafted into the district by southwest winds from the Syracuse Garbage Disposal Plant along the lake to the west, gasoline storage fumes from southeast of the lake and the proximity of two abutting cemeteries. Area warrants a second class rating because of convenience, inhabitants, stability and general desirability to class of occupant.  Typical Sales: |Address| Type Property| Sales Price & Terms| Remarks| (
